<DOCNO> APW19990406.0029 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-06 15:23:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> QB George Adjusting to New Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EDEN PRAIRIE, Minn. (AP) -- Jeff George isn't just taking a $4.6  
million pay cut to join the Minnesota Vikings. He's adjusting to a 
role he said he's never had in football: second string. 
</P>
<P>
	George signed a one-year, $400,000 contract with the Vikings on  
Tuesday. He became available when the Oakland Raiders opted out of 
his contract and signed Rich Gannon as their starting quarterback. 
</P>
<P>
	As George discussed the Vikings and his prospects for the coming  
season on Tuesday, he downplayed the pay cut and reduced role. He 
will have no problem being No. 2 behind Randall Cunningham, he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	``The future is bright whether I'm here or not,'' he said.  
``Whatever I'm asked to do is what I'm going to do.'' 
</P>
<P>
	George said he is anxious to line up behind the Vikings'  
offensive line and throw to Randy Moss, Cris Carter and Jake Reed. 
Moss and Carter made the Pro Bowl last year, along with guard 
Randall McDaniel, tackle Todd Steussie and center Jeff Christy. 
</P>
<P>
	George, who threw for 3,917 yards and 29 touchdowns as recently  
as two years ago before an injury sidelined him in the season's 
fifth week last year, said he jumped at the chance to join the 
Vikings. 
</P>
<P>
	``Money never played a part in it. I would've played for free  
here,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	George said he was excited about playing for offensive  
coordinator Ray Sherman, who was an assistant at Purdue, where 
George started his college career before transferring to Illinois. 
</P>
<P>
	The Vikings brought in the nine-year veteran, who was the first  
overall pick in the 1990 draft by the Indianapolis Colts, 
overlooking his reputation of being difficult to deal with. 
</P>
<P>
	The Atlanta Falcons released George in 1996 after he got in a  
nationally televised shouting match with coach June Jones. 
</P>
<P>
	George said he's still the same person who argued with Jones,  
but more mature. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm not going to come in here and cause trouble,'' George  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Even Jones, who now coaches at Hawaii, has only positive things  
to say about George. 
</P>
<P>
	``Jeff is, I think, probably a very misunderstood guy,'' Jones  
told the Star Tribune. ``I didn't have any problems with him other 
than that situation, and that problem was a contract problem. I 
don't think it was anything else that started that.'' 
</P>
<P>
	George said he doesn't expect to have difficulty adjusting to  
his new teammates. Most of the Vikings are scattered throughout the 
country and won't meet their new quarterback until mini-camp begins 
April 30. 
</P>
<P>
	George has never taken a team past the first round of the  
playoffs. His best postseason performance came in 1995, when he 
threw for 366 yards and two touchdowns in the Falcons' 37-20 loss 
to the Green Bay Packers at Lambeau Field. But he thinks the 
Vikings have the best chance to turn his reputation from that of a 
talented veteran known for disagreeing with his coaches into a 
winner. 
</P>
<P>
	``If you don't win a championship, you're a nobody,'' he said.  
</P>
<P>
	Despite the one-year deal, George said he plans a long stay in  
Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
	``I want to be a Viking for the rest of my career,'' he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990406.0030 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-06 15:53:04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rockies Put Walker on 15-Day DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Reigning NL batting champion Larry Walker was  
placed on the 15-day disabled list today by the Colorado Rockies, a 
week after he strained a rib cage muscle hitting a batting practice 
home run. 
</P>
<P>
	The move was retroactive to March 29, and Walker said he hopes  
to be back by next Tuesday, meaning he'll miss the first eight 
games. 
</P>
<P>
	``I didn't want to do it and still don't want to, but it's  
probably the smartest thing to do,'' Walker said before Tuesday's 
game against the San Diego Padres. 
</P>
<P>
	Walker was hurt one week earlier prior to an exhibition game. He  
worked out in San Diego on Monday, which was an off day after 
Sunday night's game against San Diego in Monterrey, Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
	``It wasn't right,'' Walker said Tuesday. ``It's a little more  
tender today.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Walker sat out Sunday night's game, missing his first opening  
day start since 1989, when he began the year in Triple-A. 
</P>
<P>
	Walker won the NL batting title last year with a .363 average,  
an encore to winning the league MVP award in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rockies purchased the contract of outfielder Mike Kelly from  
Triple-A Colorado Springs. Kelly was signed as a free agent last 
Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
