<DOCNO> APW19990406.0040 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-06 12:34:54 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Mixed; Dow Down 32.46 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks turned mixed Tuesday as an earnings  
warning from Gillette put the brakes on Monday's rally. 
</P>
<P>
	At 3 p.m. on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was  
down 32.46 at 9,974.87. The index shifted between positive and 
negative territory for much of the session, falling as much as 
69.35 points. 
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators were mixed.  
</P>
<P>
	The technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index was the brightest  
spot in the market, rising 18.48 to 2,578.54. Yahoo! provided the 
boost as traders sent its shares higher in advance of its earning 
report, due Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Many analysts believe the Web search engine company will surpass  
a First Call consensus estimate of 8 cents per share. Its stock was 
up 3 1/2 at 222 5/8 after rising 39 3/16 on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow rose 174.82 Monday to close at 10,007.33, a new record  
that marked the index's second finish above 10,000. The Nasdaq and 
S&AMP;P 500 indexes also set new records, sustained by a rally in 
Internet stocks. 
</P>
<P>
	Some traders attributed today's market dip to investors hoping  
to lock in profits from Monday's big jump. 
</P>
<P>
	Gillette, which said first-quarter profits will probably not  
meet Wall Street analysts' expectations, fell 8 1/8 today to 49 5/8. The 
company's announcement sobered traders who had bid stocks higher 
Monday on expectations of strong first-quarter results. 
</P>
<P>
	IBM rose today as the company unveiled a new version of its Web  
server, which allows companies to provide faster service on the 
Internet. IBM was up 1 1/4 at 185 3/16. 
</P>
<P>
	Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 3-to-2 margin on the  
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 625.8 million shares, 
ahead of Monday's pace. 
</P>
<P>
	The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 1.01 at 1,322.13. The  
NYSE composite index was down 1.73 at 612.90, and the American 
Stock Exchange composite index was down 2.96 at 718.28. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
