<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rodman, Actress Say Marriage is Over </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- It's back to the single life for Dennis  
Rodman. 
</P>
<P>
	The eccentric basketball star and his actress wife, Carmen  
Electra, have decided to get a divorce after less than five months 
of marriage. 
</P>
<P>
	``Carmen Electra and Dennis Rodman have announced that they have  
mutually agreed to end their ... marriage under amicable 
circumstances,'' publicist Matt Labov said Tuesday, speaking for 
both parties. ``Divorce papers were filed today in Los Angeles on 
behalf of Miss Electra. Miss Electra and Mr. Rodman are and will 
remain friends.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Rodman, 37, and Electra, 26, were wed in Las Vegas on Nov. 14  
after what was reported to be an all-night bender. Nine days later, 
Rodman claimed he was of unsound mind when he recited his vows and 
filed for an annulment. 
</P>
<P>
	However, the actress, whose real name is Tara Patrick, was with  
Rodman at Planet Hollywood in nearby Beverly Hills in February when 
he announced he was going to join the Los Angeles Lakers. 
</P>
<P>
	During that news conference, Rodman said he and his wife were  
happily married, but living in separate homes, and Electra later 
attended several games to watch her husband play. 
</P>
<P>
	Then on March 13, Rodman received permission to leave the Lakers  
to resolve personal issues, and missed four games before rejoining 
the team in Orlando on March 21. 
</P>
<P>
	The seven-time NBA rebounding champion, who has helped teams win  
five NBA championships, insisted the eight-day break had nothing to 
do with drinking, gambling, smoking or marital problems. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodman later stated it was Electra who encouraged him to return.  
</P>
<P>
	Rodman was an instant hit with fans when he joined the team,  
helping the Lakers win nine straight games. 
</P>
<P>
	However, the team's play since he returned has been  
inconsistent. One of the lowest points came Saturday night when 
Rodman was ejected after picking up two technical fouls with 2:04 
remaining in an 81-76 loss to visiting Golden State. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodman then grabbed 17 rebounds Monday night in a 117-104  
victory over Denver. Tuesday night, Rodman had 12 rebounds but did 
not score in a 106-93 loss to Utah. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990406.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-06 00:42:20 </DATE_TIME>
