<HEADLINE> Magic Announces Music Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) -- Magic Johnson's fast break into the  
music arena may have been just too quick. 
</P>
<P>
	In a news release last week, the former Los Angeles Lakers star  
announced his new venture, Magic Johnson Music Management. One of 
its first signings was the soul R&AMP;B group Boyz II Men. 
</P>
<P>
	That was news to Nathan Morris, one of the founders of the  
Grammy-winning group from Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
	Morris countered with his own news release, saying Boyz II Men  
``have not and will not be signing a management deal with Magic 
Johnson Management.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The band was sticking with the manager it had -- Quadree El-Amin  
of Southpaw Entertainment, Morris said. The original news release 
said El-Amin was joining MJM. 
</P>
<P>
	``We were shocked and upset to recently learn that the members  
of Boyz II Men had not been counseled and were not aware of their 
current management's intentions, and hope that we have not caused 
them any problems or embarrassment,'' MJM director Phil Robinson 
said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Messages left for El-Amin were not returned Monday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
