<HEADLINE> George Jones Back in Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- George Jones returned to the hospital on  
Tuesday so doctors could monitor an irregular heartbeat. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones, 67, spent two weeks at Vanderbilt University Medical  
Center after nearly dying March 6 when he smashed his vehicle into 
a bridge. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones was listed in fair condition and hoped to return home on  
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Famed for country music hits like ``He Stopped Loving Her  
Today,'' Jones suffered a collapsed lung and severely lacerated 
liver in the crash. 
</P>
<P>
	Friends said Jones was distracted while talking on a cellular  
phone, but a half-empty bottle of vodka was found in the wreckage 
and two people reported seeing Jones' vehicle weaving on the 
highway shortly before the crash. 
</P>
<P>
	A grand jury will consider next month whether Jones will face  
charges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
