<HEADLINE> Spielberg Donates To Film School </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Steven Spielberg is contributing $500,000  
toward a new generation of entertainment industry risk-takers. 
</P>
<P>
	Spielberg donated the money Tuesday to support a  
state-of-the-art, advanced-media classroom for film students at the 
University of Southern California's new Robert Zemeckis Center for 
Digital Arts. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm a long-term admirer of the hands-on education filmmakers  
receive at USC. There's no better way to learn,'' Spielberg said. 
``I imagine a new generation of creative risk-takers emerging from 
this program.'' 
</P>
