<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Man Sentenced in Valentine Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	XENIA, Ohio (AP) -- A 68-year-old man who served as his own  
lawyer was given the death sentence he wanted for killing a couple 
at a Valentine's Day dance last year. 
</P>
<P>
	Judge Thomas Rose accepted the jury's March 23 recommendation  
and on Tuesday sentenced James Taylor Sr. to death. 
</P>
<P>
	Taylor was accused of fatally shooting Ronald Rihm, 51, and  
Rihm's wife, Carolyn, 57, during a dance at an Eagles lodge in 
Fairborn in February 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutors said Taylor went to the dance to kill his estranged  
wife, Patricia, 63, who had left Taylor and moved in with the 
Rihms. She was not shot, but the Rihms were killed and another man, 
James Tipton, was wounded. 
</P>
<P>
	Taylor said he went to the dance to kill himself in front of his  
estranged wife, but the gun went off accidentally when Rihm bumped 
his arm. 
</P>
<P>
	The jury convicted Taylor of aggravated murder, attempted  
aggravated murder and attempted murder. 
</P>
<P>
	Taylor, a retired electrician with a 10th-grade education,  
repeatedly rejected the judge's suggestions that he use two 
court-appointed attorneys during the trial. Taylor relented and 
used their assistance during the penalty phase. 
</P>
<P>
	In a statement prior to sentencing, Taylor proclaimed his  
innocence and said he did not get a fair trial. He said some 
witnesses lied and that he wasn't allowed to call some of his own 
witnesses. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've been wrongly accused. I've been wrongly convicted,''  
Taylor said in a booming voice. ``You can put me to death, but 
that's all you can do after I'm dead.'' 
</P>
<P>
	His comments angered Lenora Rihm, Ronald Rihm's mother. She  
welcomed the death sentence. 
</P>
<P>
	``I wouldn't mind being there. I would watch him die,'' said  
Rihm. ``I would like to stand right over top of him and keep poking 
something in him and say, `How does it feel? How does it feel? 
You're on your way to death.''' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
