<HEADLINE> Shark Suspended for Racial Remark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- The NHL suspended San Jose Sharks defenseman  
Bryan Marchment for one game Tuesday because of ``an offensive 
comment'' to a Vancouver Canucks player. 
</P>
<P>
	Marchment served the suspension Tuesday night, sitting out the  
Sharks' game against the Phoenix Coyotes. 
</P>
<P>
	During the second period of a 5-2 victory over the Canucks on  
Saturday in San Jose, Marchment called Donald Brashears, who is 
black, a ``monkey.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``Mr. Marchment has admitted making the remark,'' NHL hockey  
operations director Colin Campbell said. ``While we accept that 
there was no inappropriate intent on Mr. Marchment's part, we 
cannot excuse the conduct.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
