<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Boeing Rocket Launch Delayed Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. (AP) -- For the second night in a row,  
Boeing delayed the launch of its new Delta III rocket Tuesday, this 
time because of technical trouble. 
</P>
<P>
	Boeing must wait until next week to try again because other  
rockets need to be launched from Cape Canaveral Air Station. 
Monday's try was thwarted by the wind. 
</P>
<P>
	The rocket holds a communication satellite that will serve Asia  
and the Pacific region. 
</P>
<P>
	The countdown was halted Tuesday at the 25-second mark when a  
valve became stuck and an unrelated red alarm went off. Alarms also 
had gone off minutes earlier. Launch controllers solved all those 
problems, but then a radar-tracking station went down and the team 
ran out of time. 
</P>
<P>
	The Delta III's inaugural flight last August ended in an  
explosion shortly after liftoff. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
