<HEADLINE> Hawks' Ellis Out for Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- LaPhonso Ellis of the Atlanta Hawks will miss the  
rest of the season because of a sports hernia that will require 
surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	Ellis, on the injured list since March 14, originally was  
diagnosed with back spasms, but because he was showing no 
improvement and the pain had not subsided, team trainers took him 
to a back specialist who in turn sent Ellis to a hernia specialist. 
</P>
<P>
	The hernia is high on the left side and the Hawks said Tuesday  
the specialist thinks the injury may have been the byproduct of hip 
surgery a few years ago when some bone was removed, possibly 
weakening his body. 
</P>
<P>
	Ellis, in his first year with the Hawks after six seasons with  
Denver, had started 20 games before being sidelined. He was 
averaging 10.2 points and 5.4 rebounds per game. He was signed as a 
free agent to a two-year contract. 
</P>
</TEXT>
