<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Dow Ends Down 43.84 at 9,963.49  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mostly lower today as an earnings  
warning from Gillette put the brakes on yesterday's rally. At the 
close on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was down 
43.84 at 9,963.49. The index shifted between positive and negative 
territory for much of the session, rising as much as 23 points in 
choppy trading. Broader stock indicators were mixed. The 
technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index was the brightest spot in 
the market for much of the session before giving up most of its 
gains in the last hour of trading. It was up 3.11 at 2,563.17. The 
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 was down 3.23 at 1,317.89. Some traders 
attributed today's market dip also to investors hoping to lock in 
profits from yesterday's jump that took the Dow to a record high 
close: up 174.82 at 10,007.33. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
