<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-06 05:55:05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Brit Air Offers Loans to Passengers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- British Airways is trying to give business a lift  
by offering to help customers pay for their flights. 
</P>
<P>
	The airline began Tuesday offering travel loans of between $800  
to $24,000 to make it easier for people to splurge on their 
vacations. 
</P>
<P>
	The loans carry a 15.9 percent annual interest rate, and  
borrowers will have up to two years to repay. Customers also will 
have the option of repaying their loans within three months without 
interest. 
</P>
<P>
	British Airways said it is the first airline to offer such a  
service. The loans are currently available at six of the company's 
travel shops in Britain. 
</P>
<P>
	British Airways hopes the offer will appeal to customers by  
making it easier for them to plan and book holiday flights, said a 
spokeswoman, Sara Jones. ``Obviously it would attract new customers 
as well,'' she said. 
</P>
<P>
	If the program catches on, British Airways will make it  
available at all of its 23 travel shops in Britain. The airline is 
working with Abbey National Group to provide the loans. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
