<HEADLINE> Toyota To Expand in N. America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ERLANGER, Ky. (AP) -- Toyota Motor Manufacturing North America  
Inc. will expand its northern Kentucky headquarters, company 
officials announced today. 
</P>
<P>
	The $15.4 million project will add 80,000 square feet,  
increasing the facility's size to 258,000 square feet. 
</P>
<P>
	Toyota already has expanded the facility once since locating in  
Erlanger in 1996. Last year, a laboratory for quality and 
production engineering activities opened at the site. 
</P>
<P>
	The expansion will increase the number of work stations and  
conference rooms, and provide space for a cafeteria. Workers who 
had been using a leased building nearby will be moved to the main 
facility after the expansion. 
</P>
<P>
	``In our two and a half years in operation here, we have  
continued to absorb administrative functions'' that were handled in 
japan and at other North American facilities, said Teruyuki 
Minoura, president and chief executive of TMMNA. ``As a result, our 
full-time employment at Erlanger will grow to 700 team members, and 
we have to expand existing work and meeting space.'' 
</P>
<P>
	At present, 630 people are employed at the facility.  
</P>
</TEXT>
