<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Padres Put Myers on 15-day DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Padres reliever Randy Myers was placed on the  
15-day disabled list today with a strained left rotator cuff. The 
move is retroactive to Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Myers, who underwent an MRI exam on Monday, was unable to warm  
up during San Diego's season opener on Sunday night against the 
Colorado Rockies at Monterrey, Mexico. He lacked velocity in spring 
training, when the Padres continued to try to trade him. 
</P>
<P>
	San Diego gambled by acquiring Myers in a waiver deal with  
Toronto on Aug. 6. Normally a closer, he was used in a setup role 
because the Padres had one of baseball's top closers in Trevor 
Hoffman. The Padres made it an offseason priority to trade him 
because he's due more than $12 million in the final two years of 
his contract. With a salary of $6 million, he is the highest-paid 
Padres player this season. 
</P>
<P>
	The Padres purchased the contract of left-hander Roberto Rivera  
from Class AAA Las Vegas. To make room for Rivera on the 40-man 
roster, the Padres designated infielder Ed Giovanola for 
assignment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
