<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mass. Man Pleads Guilty to Abuse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW BEDFORD, Mass. (AP) -- A man pleaded guilty Tuesday to  
torturing two retarded men with hammers, pliers and sticks and 
scalding them with water. 
</P>
<P>
	Karol Simonton, 62, was in his second day of trial when he  
decided to admit to raping, beating and starving the men regularly, 
stealing their Social Security money and forcing them to panhandle. 
</P>
<P>
	The state Department of Mental Retardation came under fire after  
the abuse was revealed in February 1997 and a supervisor was 
suspended for 10 days. 
</P>
<P>
	``They didn't live as well as the dogs lived in the house,''  
prosecutor Walter Shea said of the victims, now age 63 and 26. 
</P>
<P>
	Simonton will be sentenced April 27.  
</P>
<P>
	On the rape charges alone he could face up to 60 years in  
prison. Simonton's brother, Harold, is also accused and scheduled 
to go to trial later in the week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
