<HEADLINE> Doctors: Farrakhan Is Cancer-Free </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Doctors for Nation of Islam leader Louis  
Farrakhan today proclaimed him cured of the prostate cancer for 
which he has been treated since 1991. 
</P>
<P>
	Farrakhan was admitted to Howard University Hospital on an  
emergency basis last week and underwent surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	Abdul Alim Muhammad, health minister for the Nation of Islam,  
said Farrakhan's surgery was to correct an inflammation of his 
rectal wall, a side effect of eight years of treatment for cancer. 
</P>
<P>
	Muhammad and Alfred Goldson, who heads the radiology oncology  
department at Howard University Hospital, said a battery of tests 
on Farrakhan including bone scans and a test for prostate specific 
antigen (PSA) showed he is free of cancer. 
</P>
<P>
	``There is absolutely no evidence of any cancer in his body,''  
Muhammad said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
