<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-06 13:25:09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Doctor Accused of Raping MS Patient </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ELYRIA, Ohio (AP) -- A doctor has been charged with raping and  
fondling a multiple sclerosis patient while she was in intensive 
care. 
</P>
<P>
	Dr. Ashok Ramadugu, 40, was arrested Monday and freed on $50,000  
bail. 
</P>
<P>
	Ramadugu helped treat the woman, then 22, last spring while she  
was at EMH Regional Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
	``She was not totally aware of what was happening'' because of  
her condition, Prosecutor Gregory A. White said. 
</P>
<P>
	Ramadugu has requested a leave of absence from the hospital. A  
call to his lawyer was not returned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
